        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-05-06T13:16:15.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"10\" data-topic=\"160746\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"6\" data-topic=\"160746\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>I have tasted a few 2019s, including my own Chambolle-Musigny</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Are you getting into the n\u00e9goce game?!</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I make just two barrels of Chambolle-Musigny for fun. I\u2019m finding it\u2019s a great way to learn about each new vintage, so it complements my day job rather than distracts from it. My dream retirement project is getting together a few hectares and making my own wine.</p>",
